               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_322-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="en">An anthology of prose and poetry.</title>
                     <note>The manuscript is formed of sections written in more than one hand and of varying formats. F1a: a) Signature of David Price. b) Note of price of 3 rupees. Three folios after the final poem contain prayers and recipes, including two formulae for colouring Bidri ware. Back flyleaf, verso: Couplet lamenting the death of Tipu Sultan dated A.H. 1214 (1799-1800), the text defective. Includes pieces by Zuhuri, Tughra'i Mashhadi, 'Urfi, Abu 'l-Fadl, Mir Walihi Qummi, Nizam al-Mulk, Nasira-yi Hamadani, Baba Afdal and many others. Red headings and punctuation in parts. Scribe for the first uniform section and again later: Ibn Sadr al-Din Muhammad Baqir al-'Aqili al-Adhami al-Imami al-Isfahani.</note>
                     <incipit>Surud-sarayan-i anjuman-i 'ishratgah- qal.</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a list of the manuscripts bequeathed by Price and a notice on him see J.R.A.S. iii (1836), pp. xii, lx.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
